snippet.title: original song: “yellow brick road” *ROUGH VERSION*
snippet.description:
Lyrics:

wish you could have come with me 
over the yellow brick road
I’ve grown a bean stock with my seeds 
but now I don’t see you anymore 

It’s so sad 
that you couldn’t come with me 
changing so fast 
that you couldn’t catch me 

I’ll be at the end of the yellow brick road,
do you want to go?

wish you could have seen 
all your glory, all you did for me
you carry the weight of the world 
it must be heavy 

but now, it’s so sad 
that you couldn’t come with me
changing so fast 
that you couldn’t catch me 

I’ll be at the end of the yellow brick road,
do you want to go?

I loved you so bad 
that I was blind to see 
I wasn’t letting you be 

I’m sorry I had to let you go
I had to pave the way, there was no gold 
will you follow the yellow brick road?
will you follow the yellow brick road?
